THE WYOMING. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 30, 1907.) No. 127. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. Herbert Green, and Wilcox & Green, for appellant. Chas. C. Burlingham and Wing, Putnam & Burlingham, for appellees.

Before Judges WALLACE, LACOMBE, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree of District Court (145 Fed. 735) affirmed, with interest and costs.
